title: What might cause poor quality of online streaming media played on my phone?
answer:
The source streaming media is of poor quality. 

 The network connection is poor. 

 Your phone's hardware may be faulty, for example, the display is damaged. To check whether your phone's hardware is faulty, play a local video for comparison. 

 Your phone's available memory is insufficient. 

 The CPU usage is high. 

 Too many applications are running. 

 [The power saving mode is not set to normal.]()
